<dl id="n08048e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08048e">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08048e"> 48(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> in trying to hide / his face revealed / his cazzo</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Heureusement, la multiplicit&eacute; des mouvements graphiques est telle, qu&apos;il appara&icirc;t toujours quelque chose de la v&eacute;ritable personnalit&eacute; du scripteur, m&ecirc;me dans l&apos;&eacute;criture volontairement d&eacute;guis&eacute;e. <mark>Veut-on dissimuler un trace? Il en &eacute;chappe un autre &eacute;quivalent</mark>. <br><font color="green">[Luckily, there are so many graphic movements, that something of the real personality of the writer always appears, even in writing that is deliberately disguised. We try to conceal a trait? An equivalent trait appears elsewhere.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) ?275</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
